<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1943486-i-literally-can-t-understand-the-language">I literally can&#39;t understand the language of this book, I thought Scottish accent was just the way they speak but turns out it&#39;s not. How do you read this and what can I do to understand it?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1943486'><a id="like_count_community_question_1943486" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1943486?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F135836.Trainspotting">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1943486-i-literally-can-t-understand-the-language">one year ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1943486-i-literally-can-t-understand-the-language">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/30598594-alexey-varfolomeev"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_100x100-c7bfe730633c9983e27caaa66a8e244a.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/30598594-alexey-varfolomeev">Alexey Varfolomeev</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I&apos;d say you get used to it. The differences mostly cover auxiliary verbs, pronouns, and prepositions, and there are not many of those, so before long <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I'd say you get used to it. The differences mostly cover auxiliary verbs, pronouns, and prepositions, and there are not many of those, so before long you acquire an automatic understanding of what it is what.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
