        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3769152474" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4485039282554572789">Edinburgh, a sick city, the 1990s. While the industrial and employment crisis raged in these post-Tatchérien years, a group of lost friends survived. This world revolves around dope: heroin, cocaine, weed, alcohol, H, barbiturates, clusters of asteroids in perdition, attracted by the fatal orbit of the powder which is nothing like stardust. Fixed that we lavish ourselves in mock hugs convulsed with pleasure, humiliating pleas to the local dealer for adulterated merchandise, calamitous weaning at</span>
  <span id="freeText4485039282554572789" style="display:none">Edinburgh, a sick city, the 1990s. While the industrial and employment crisis raged in these post-Tatchérien years, a group of lost friends survived. This world revolves around dope: heroin, cocaine, weed, alcohol, H, barbiturates, clusters of asteroids in perdition, attracted by the fatal orbit of the powder which is nothing like stardust. Fixed that we lavish ourselves in mock hugs convulsed with pleasure, humiliating pleas to the local dealer for adulterated merchandise, calamitous weaning attempts, doomed rehabilitations, junky's dilemma, overdoses, bad trips, premature deaths, the spectre of AIDS, trouble with the law following miserable theft to the detriment of small local traders, fights in pubs, football derbies that turn into settling of scores, the life without the perspective of these boys is perilous.<br />On a soundtrack of brit-pop music, this polyphonic novel alternates first-person stories emanating from the various acolytes of this band of chronically unsuitable endearing and distanced stories the third person of the singular, in a very slang and filthy language. Colourful and suggestive, striking and effective like a ball in the face, the alternating difference in tones, disillusioned humour and self-mockery fully deserves its reputation as a cult book of the 90s.</span>
